 586:src/main.cpp  **** // glide_ms / attack_ms / release_ms), converted to coefficients in the audio
 587:src/main.cpp  **** // callback. The constants below are the ones still shared by all voices.
 588:src/main.cpp  **** // Cutoff opening slew. The target is recomputed only at the touch-loop rate
 589:src/main.cpp  **** // (~12-16 Hz) and pressure is quantized to integer %, so a too-fast slew lets
 590:src/main.cpp  **** // each coarse step through as zipper/stair-stepping. ~35 ms interpolates across
 591:src/main.cpp  **** // those steps for a smooth filter sweep while still feeling responsive.
 592:src/main.cpp  **** static constexpr float SLEW_CUT    = 0.9994f; // filter cutoff ‚Äî ~35 ms smooth
